long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I ran 'dnf update -y' on my Rawhide box.
Version-Release number of selected component: dnf-2.0.0-0.rc1.4.fc26
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0.63.g6a16.dirty cmdline: /usr/libexec/system-python /usr/bin/dnf update -y crash_function: _scriptError exception_type: AttributeError executable: /usr/bin/dnf kernel: 4.8.0-0.rc8.git0.1.fc26.x86_64 runlevel: N 5 type: Python3 uid: 0
Truncated backtrace: rpmtrans.py:550:_scriptError:AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'name'
Traceback (most recent call last): File "/usr/lib/python3.5/site-packages/dnf/yum/rpmtrans.py", line 426, in callback self._scriptError(amount, total, key) File "/usr/lib/python3.5/site-packages/dnf/yum/rpmtrans.py", line 550, in _scriptError name = pkg.name AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'name'
Local variables in innermost frame: scriptlet_name: 'POSTUN' key: 'binutils' amount: 1026 _: None self: <dnf.yum.rpmtrans.RPMTransaction object at 0x7efd5c8fb940> total: 0 pkg: None

This bug was created by attempt to fix bug: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1382866 by commit https://github.com/rpm-software-management/dnf/commit/507acfe3c0f81f253621d116a7474e1081d979f5
*** Bug 1323552 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
Planned to be fixed next month.
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.
I create a pull-request that will prevent the problem: https://github.com/rpm-software-management/dnf/pull/754
